An MLFB player for the Virginia Armada to @WKRG‚Äôs @74Talk: ‚ÄúCoach (Terry) Shea is a great dude, he was willing to pay out of his own pocket to make sure his players have one more night. (In hotel) Something you‚Äôve got to respect, be grateful for bc other teams are scrambling‚Ä¶‚Äù

‚ÄúIf it wasn‚Äôt for Coach Shea, there would be a real problem.‚Äù 

‚ÄúAt this point, we are just controlling what we can control.‚Äù

‚ÄúWe are just staying on standby, they may bring us back in a couple of weeks. To be honest, it‚Äôs just part of the business, so you gotta understand how it goes. It may not fall how you want it to, but you have to keep going.‚Äù

‚ÄúWe are just playing it by year, they really haven‚Äôt told us much so we can‚Äôt really go off much. We signed our contract, fulfilled our part of the deal. People still have to pay for their own flights and stuff too.‚Äù

‚ÄúIt‚Äôs back to XFL or the USFL or even NFL. Once they start to see this, they may offer some of us to go to training camps. Every player here is trying to get to the next level, we are grinding regardless.‚Äù
‚ÄúCoach Shea just saying he has faith in the owner, it‚Äôs suspended, but he feels like he will be able to get everything situated.‚Äù

‚ÄúIt‚Äôs not the coaches fault, the players fault, it‚Äôs the owner. Until he can be able to fix his situation, we don‚Äôt know what‚Äôs going on‚Ä¶ right now, everybody thinking ‚Äòshoot we gotta go back home‚Äô and pretty much go back to the drawing board.‚Äù

On Coach Shea: 

‚ÄúHe‚Äôs a great dude, he was willing to pay out of his own pocket to make sure his players have at least one more night to stay. That‚Äôs something you have to be grateful for. There‚Äôs other teams staying at the [Ladd-Peebles] stadium.‚Äù
‚ÄúI don‚Äôt want to say ‚ÄòI knew this was coming‚Äô but it‚Äôs like, I knew this was one of the possibilities.‚Äù

‚Ä¶we start hearing about the owner owing lots of money to the hotels and stuff. Once you hear that, you know where it‚Äôs gonna go. Coaches scrambling around, so you pretty much know some bad news is about to come.‚Äù

The three players I spoke with wish to stay anonymous. Here a few quotes from what was talked about: 

‚ÄúWe just didn‚Äôt know, it caught us off guard. We thought we were gonna have meetings and then we go to our room and we have to check out. Once we get down to the lobby‚Ä¶

I‚Äôm here at the Virginia Armada team hotel in Mobile. 

I spoke to a few players on the team  regarding the recent news of @MLFBofficial not paying for its teams hotel rooms. 

Head Coach Terry Shea has elected to pay for his players to stay in the hotel. The length is TBD.

Corte also said they required MLFB to ‚Äúprepay‚Äù rental fees for use of Ladd-Peebles Stadium.

‚ÄúLadd-Peebles Stadium did receive the $30,000 non-refundable rental fee, which satisfied the Ladd contract, before the teams started training camp practices July 18th‚Ä¶
